olumn":8,"offset":345},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The oldest kind of leverage is labor. Having a couple of people carry stones will do it quicker than you alone. Being the oldest kind of leverage means it's recognized and overvalued in society. E.g. impressed parents when you get promoted to a management function and you have people working for you now. But managing people is messy and takes a lot of time and leadership skills, so it doesn't scale well.","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":349},"end":{"line":13,"column":408,"offset":756},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":349},"end":{"line":13,"column":408,"offset":756},"indent":[]}},{"type":"heading","depth":1,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Capital","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":3,"offset":762},"end":{"line":15,"column":10,"offset":769},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":760},"end":{"line":15,"column":10,"offset":769},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Capital is another form of old leverage. It scales much better than labor but is hard to get. It requires you to be a ","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1,"offset":773},"end":{"line":17,"column":119,"offset":891},"indent":[]}},{"type":"link","title":null,"url":"/accountability","children":[{"type":"text","value":"credible person","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":120,"offset":892},"end":{"line":17,"column":135,"offset":907},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":119,"offset":891},"end":{"line":17,"column":153,"offset":925},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" and have specific knowledge of a domain. But if you have this then people will give you capital as a form of leverage. You can scale capital very well. You can convert it to labor and other services. Most of the rich non-tech companies got rich by using capital as leverage.","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":153,"offset":925},"end":{"line":17,"column":428,"offset":1200},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1,"offset":773},"end":{"line":17,"column":428,"offset":1200},"indent":[]}},{"type":"heading","depth":1,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Product and media","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":3,"offset":1206},"end":{"line":19,"column":20,"offset":1223},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1,"offset":1204},"end":{"line":19,"column":20,"offset":1223},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"New forms of leverage are product and media. They have no marginal costs of replication and don't need permission. You can code, build products, create podcasts, tweet, etc without anyone's permission. E.g. Before you needed to get permission to be on tv and it would leverage their channel, not yours.","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1,"offset":1227},"end":{"line":21,"column":303,"offset":1529},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1,"offset":1227},"end":{"line":21,"column":303,"offset":1529},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Product and media will work for you while you sleep.","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1,"offset":1533},"end":{"line":23,"column":53,"offset":1585},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1,"offset":1533},"end":{"line":23,"column":53,"offset":1585},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"All the new rich of late use this form of leverage. Examples of products are Google, Amazon, and Microsoft. Examples of media are Joe Rogan and Pewdiepie.","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1,"offset":1589},"end":{"line":25,"column":155,"offset":1743},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1,"offset":1589},"end":{"line":25,"column":155,"offset":1743},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Combining all forms of leverage is the magic combination. E.g. tech companies use engineers and designers as labor. Capital for marketing, advertising, and scaling. Media are podcasts and blogs and coded products.","position":{"start":{"line":27,"column":1,"offset":1747},"end":{"line":27,"column":214,"offset":1960},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":27,"column":1,"offset":1747},"end":{"line":27,"column":214,"offset":1960},"indent":[]}},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Robots","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":4,"offset":1967},"end":{"line":29,"column":10,"offset":1973},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1,"offset":1964},"end":{"line":29,"column":10,"offset":1973},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Robots are the ultimate form of leverage and they've been here a while - just not in physical form. It's all in code. These programs perform your tasks while you sleep. While running on servers. These robots work 24/7 and if you can code, you can command an army of robots doing the work for you.","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1,"offset":1977},"end":{"line":31,"column":297,"offset":2273},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1,"offset":1977},"end":{"line":31,"column":297,"offset":2273},"indent":[]}},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Products","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":4,"offset":2280},"end":{"line":33,"column":12,"offset":2288},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1,"offset":2277},"end":{"line":33,"column":12,"offset":2288},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Certain expensive products are only served for the upper class, like Rolex and Lamborghini. The upperclass uses these products to signal their wealth and status. They're made more expensive, so only a select few can buy them. They're nothing but status products (in a ","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1,"offset":2292},"end":{"line":35,"column":269,"o